339
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:22,920
I'll sleep...

340
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:25,320
I'll sleep in the guest room.

341
00:22:26,040 --> 00:22:27,160
The guest room.

342
00:22:27,720 --> 00:22:29,320
-I'll sleep...
-Mumu.

343
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:32,640
The guest room.

344
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:13,760
<i>Mumu, are you up yet?</i>

345
00:23:16,680 --> 00:23:17,720
Mumu?

346
00:23:18,320 --> 00:23:19,600
Move in with me.

347
00:23:20,360 --> 00:23:22,960
Are you going to kiss me?

348
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:26,400
We can't become too close.

349
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:32,960
This is bad.

350
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:35,800
What have I done?

351
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:42,200
<i>I'm up.</i>

352
00:23:47,360 --> 00:23:49,360
<i>Have you thought about
what I asked you yesterday?</i>

353
00:23:51,040 --> 00:23:52,680
<i>Yesterday?</i>

354
00:23:58,480 --> 00:24:00,200
What?

355
00:24:01,120 --> 00:24:04,400
Mr. Ling asked you to live with him?

356
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:09,200
I've been a bit slow on the uptake lately.

357
00:24:09,280 --> 00:24:10,680
Give me a minute.

358
00:24:14,280 --> 00:24:16,520
As a screenwriter,
I'm obligated to tell you

359
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:18,920
what is bound to happen
after you move in with him.

360
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:19,880
What?

361
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:21,560
After you move in together,

362
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:24,760
both of you will reveal your true selves

363
00:24:25,120 --> 00:24:26,920
and see a side of the other person

364
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:29,360
that you wouldn't normally see.

365
00:24:29,640 --> 00:24:30,640
At the same time,

366
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:34,320
you'll gain a deeper understanding
of each other.

367
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:39,120
Finally, from a certain birthmark
or distinguishing feature,

368
00:24:39,480 --> 00:24:41,680
you'll realize that

369
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:45,360
you two are actually long-lost siblings!

370
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:46,920
My goodness.

371
00:24:47,040 --> 00:24:49,000
Can you be more helpful?

372
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:52,160
Well, after you two move in together,

373
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:55,240
you'll be spending time
with each other day and night.

374
00:24:55,360 --> 00:24:57,000
First, on a material level.

375
00:24:57,160 --> 00:25:00,520
You'll learn more
about each other's preferences.

376
00:25:00,720 --> 00:25:03,120
Next, on a mental level.

377
00:25:03,440 --> 00:25:05,880
You'll know each other better.

378
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:10,560
In the process of doing so,
you understand yourself even better.

379
00:25:10,640 --> 00:25:12,320
-I see.
-Lastly

380
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:15,120
and most importantly

381
00:25:15,520 --> 00:25:17,040
is the physical level.

382
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:20,960
By living together,
you'll be at each other's side

383
00:25:21,120 --> 00:25:23,960
find perfect harmony,
feel the sparks of passion

384
00:25:24,040 --> 00:25:26,560
-and enjoy carnal intimacy!
-Stop!

385
00:25:28,880 --> 00:25:31,240
Can you stop making it sound so sensual?

386
00:25:31,960 --> 00:25:33,160
The viewers like it.

387
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:37,400
Let's get back on topic.

388
00:25:37,960 --> 00:25:40,280
Why are you rejecting Mr. Ling?

389
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:43,960
He's handsome, comes from a good family
and devoted to you.

390
00:25:44,600 --> 00:25:47,120
Isn't he the perfect husband?

391
00:25:47,360 --> 00:25:48,560
Why are you rejecting him?

392
00:25:52,560 --> 00:25:54,560
The perfect husband?

393
00:25:59,960 --> 00:26:00,840
And...

394
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:04,360
You should spice up your lingerie.

395
00:26:15,320 --> 00:26:16,240
What's up?

396
00:26:17,440 --> 00:26:19,160
The contract has been signed.
There are no issues.

397
00:26:19,240 --> 00:26:21,760
The first meeting you're holding
is scheduled for 2 p.m. tomorrow.

398
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:25,040
Due to work conflicts, two board members
will join via video conference.

399
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:27,480
Okay, I understand.

400
00:26:27,920 --> 00:26:28,840
One more thing.

401
00:26:29,480 --> 00:26:34,840
Don't let the board know
about the contract with Risheng yet.

402
00:26:35,040 --> 00:26:36,000
Yes, Boss.

403
00:26:36,200 --> 00:26:37,040
One more thing.

404
00:26:41,280 --> 00:26:42,400
I heard...

405
00:26:43,320 --> 00:26:45,200
something happened
between you and Ms. Jia.

406
00:26:49,200 --> 00:26:51,040
You know about that, Boss?

407
00:26:51,680 --> 00:26:52,680
It's okay.

408
00:26:55,160 --> 00:26:56,640
Remember, safety first.

409
00:26:56,920 --> 00:26:58,360
Use protection.

410
00:26:58,880 --> 00:26:59,800
Okay.

411
00:27:09,120 --> 00:27:11,400
<i>The first meeting you're holding
is scheduled for 2 p.m. tomorrow.</i>

412
00:27:11,480 --> 00:27:14,440
<i>Due to work conflicts, two board members
will join via video conference.</i>

413
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:16,800
<i>Okay, I understand.</i>

414
00:27:17,240 --> 00:27:18,240
<i>One more thing.</i>

415
00:27:18,800 --> 00:27:24,280
<i>Don't let the board know
about the contract with Risheng yet.</i>

416
00:27:33,600 --> 00:27:36,600
Mr. Fu, don't tell me
it's a coincidence that you're here too.

417
00:27:37,160 --> 00:27:39,120
I came to see you, Ms. Jiang.

418
00:27:43,120 --> 00:27:46,360
Why is an attorney
acting like a paparazzo?

419
00:27:46,720 --> 00:27:47,760
Are you following me?

420
00:27:48,520 --> 00:27:50,000
You're funny, Ms. Jiang.

421
00:27:51,200 --> 00:27:54,080
This document is likely
very important to you.

422
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:55,800
Take a look.

423
00:27:59,120 --> 00:28:00,160
INVESTIGATION REVEALS

424
00:28:00,240 --> 00:28:01,680
LOCAL THUGS INVOLVED IN A HIT-AND-RUN

425
00:28:06,680 --> 00:28:08,000
A CAR ACCIDENT OCCURRED

426
00:28:08,080 --> 00:28:09,600
IN BINYI DISTRICT OF THE CITY OF GANGDONG

427
00:28:14,600 --> 00:28:16,400
I'm sure you didn't just show me this

428
00:28:17,040 --> 00:28:19,480
to tell me the truth about what happened.

429
00:28:19,880 --> 00:28:21,760
You're a very smart lady.

430
00:28:22,280 --> 00:28:24,200
What do you want me to do?

431
00:28:24,480 --> 00:28:28,920
I hope you'll help me deliver this gift.

432
00:28:55,320 --> 00:28:56,560
NING LAN

433
00:28:56,640 --> 00:28:59,440
SURVIVING SON, FU WEINING,
LAID TO REST ON JULY 5, 2017

434
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:45,080
Hello?

435
00:29:46,960 --> 00:29:47,920
<i>Weining?</i>

436
00:29:48,520 --> 00:29:50,160
<i>Your mom passed away peacefully,</i>

437
00:29:50,720 --> 00:29:52,120
<i>but she kept talking about you.</i>

438
00:29:54,080 --> 00:29:55,960
<i>Weining, come home.</i>

439
00:29:56,440 --> 00:29:57,960
<i>Pay your last respects.</i>

440
00:30:10,280 --> 00:30:11,160
<i>Mom.</i>

441
00:30:11,240 --> 00:30:13,160
<i>The kitchen was so hot
on the day you passed away.</i>

442
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:14,280
<i> I miss you.</i>

443
00:30:14,560 --> 00:30:17,160
<i>I've accomplished everything
that I promised you.</i>

444
00:30:19,520 --> 00:30:21,320
<i>It's a few years later
than I had planned though.</i>

445
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:23,680
<i>I wish you were here.</i>

446
00:30:28,360 --> 00:30:30,480
<i>Mom, I'm leaving now.</i>

447
00:30:31,520 --> 00:30:34,320
<i>I'll bring good news
the next time I visit.</i>

448
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:51,080
Let's see how he'll explain this time.

449
00:30:51,720 --> 00:30:53,280
-Hello, everybody.
-There he is.

450
00:30:53,960 --> 00:30:56,360
I called this meeting today
for two reasons.

451
00:30:57,600 --> 00:31:01,280
The first reason is to put an end
to what happened a while ago.

452
00:31:03,120 --> 00:31:05,920
-What's going on?
-What you are about to receive

453
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:07,760
is an investigation report on complaints

454
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:09,400
of my alleged misconduct.

455
00:31:10,480 --> 00:31:11,400
The second document

456
00:31:11,520 --> 00:31:13,880
is a contract with a foreign entity
for additional investment.

457
00:31:14,800 --> 00:31:19,000
An internal audit confirmed that I did not
engage in any illicit competition.

458
00:31:19,160 --> 00:31:20,960
Someone else
will report the details in a bit.

459
00:31:21,200 --> 00:31:23,160
I have begun to gather evidence

460
00:31:23,240 --> 00:31:26,240
for a legal case against the person
who accused and maligned me.

461
00:31:27,840 --> 00:31:29,120
In that case,

462
00:31:29,560 --> 00:31:32,400
can you explain

463
00:31:33,280 --> 00:31:36,680
why you signed
an acquisition agreement with Risheng

464
00:31:37,640 --> 00:31:41,440
without first getting a vote
by the Board of Directors?

465
00:31:41,840 --> 00:31:43,520
-Exactly.
-This is a serious decision.

466
00:31:43,800 --> 00:31:46,000
Don't board members have a right to know?

467
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:50,320
-Yes.
-Agreed.

468
00:31:50,400 --> 00:31:52,520
If I hadn't been tipped off,

469
00:31:53,320 --> 00:31:56,600
I would have been kept in the dark
like the rest of you.

470
00:31:57,000 --> 00:31:58,600
-Is that true?
-This isn't right.

471
00:31:58,680 --> 00:32:00,400
While the Internal Audit Department

472
00:32:00,480 --> 00:32:02,680
has been investigating
Mr. Ling's misconduct,

473
00:32:02,840 --> 00:32:04,040
someone discovered

474
00:32:04,360 --> 00:32:06,880
that Mr. Ling had already signed

475
00:32:06,960 --> 00:32:09,520
an agreement to acquire Risheng Retail.

476
00:32:10,920 --> 00:32:12,000
-What?
-There's more.

477
00:32:12,200 --> 00:32:15,080
This deal exceeds ten billion yuan!

478
00:32:15,320 --> 00:32:16,960
-Ten billion?
-That's an enormous sum!

479
00:32:17,400 --> 00:32:19,200
Mr. Ling's arbitrary decision

480
00:32:19,440 --> 00:32:21,560
not only violates company policy,

481
00:32:21,880 --> 00:32:24,480
but will also cause monumental losses

482
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:26,280
for us and the company!

483
00:32:26,600 --> 00:32:28,200
-You're right.
-Mr. Ling.

484
00:32:28,720 --> 00:32:30,400
How do you explain this?

485
00:32:33,280 --> 00:32:36,960
I gathered all of you here today
to hear your opinions.

486
00:32:39,320 --> 00:32:42,040
You already made your decision
and signed the contract.

487
00:32:42,120 --> 00:32:43,840
Now you're asking for our opinions?

488
00:32:44,240 --> 00:32:45,680
-That's right.
-Isn't it too late?

489
00:32:46,120 --> 00:32:47,800
It has already been done.

490
00:32:48,720 --> 00:32:49,920
Please do not worry.

491
00:32:50,960 --> 00:32:54,840
The acquisition of Risheng Retail
was always part of our annual plan.

492
00:32:55,080 --> 00:32:57,880
That's still not a reason for you
to sign the contract on your own!

493
00:33:00,400 --> 00:33:04,520
Mr. Jin, where did you receive the intel
that the deal has been closed?

494
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:08,400
You shouldn't have done it
if you didn't want anyone to know.

495
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:10,960
It won't be difficult to prove it.

496
00:33:11,520 --> 00:33:14,840
All contracts have to pass through
our Legal Department.

497
00:33:14,920 --> 00:33:16,480
-That's right.
-Call in someone from Legal.

498
00:33:16,560 --> 00:33:17,440
-We'll know then.
-Right.

499
00:33:17,520 --> 00:33:18,880
-That won't be necessary.
-Yes.

500
00:33:18,960 --> 00:33:20,120
I came prepared.

501
00:33:20,320 --> 00:33:23,000
Flip to page five of the document
in front of you.

502
00:33:24,480 --> 00:33:25,840
What you're seeing

503
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:28,040
is the motion for a cash acquisition

504
00:33:28,120 --> 00:33:30,160
for 78 percent of Risheng's shares.

505
00:33:30,320 --> 00:33:32,800
Mr. Jin's claim that
the deal has been closed

506
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:34,840
is merely hearsay.

507
00:33:36,280 --> 00:33:37,760
I believe you are all aware

508
00:33:38,200 --> 00:33:40,040
that we have strong competition
this time around.

509
00:33:40,240 --> 00:33:43,000
That is why I began negotiations
with the target company in advance.

510
00:33:43,320 --> 00:33:45,720
They have confidence
in Lingshi Group's integration capability

511
00:33:45,800 --> 00:33:47,720
and have provided a nice valuation.

512
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:49,920
We just need a board vote

513
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:51,360
to complete the acquisition.

514
00:33:52,000 --> 00:33:54,480
The process does not violate any policies.

515
00:33:54,960 --> 00:33:56,880
Is that clear, Mr. Jin?

516
00:33:57,520 --> 00:33:58,440
This...

517
00:33:58,840 --> 00:34:00,640
This can't be.

518
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:02,400
I told you it was nothing.

519
00:34:02,640 --> 00:34:06,080
Mr. Ling wouldn't act
against the interests of the company.

520
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:08,120
-Yes.
-Thank you for your trust in me.

521
00:34:09,400 --> 00:34:11,320
I also hope that you will all continue

522
00:34:11,440 --> 00:34:13,800
to support and believe in
Lingshi Group's development.

523
00:34:14,239 --> 00:34:16,639
If anybody wishes
to strike out on their own,

524
00:34:16,800 --> 00:34:18,120
I will not force them to stay.

525
00:34:18,679 --> 00:34:20,400
Right, Mr. Jin?

526
00:34:22,560 --> 00:34:23,600
All right,

527
00:34:23,679 --> 00:34:25,920
today's meeting is adjourned.

528
00:34:26,040 --> 00:34:28,280
We will conduct a vote next time.

529
00:34:38,080 --> 00:34:39,800
How do you explain this?

530
00:34:40,440 --> 00:34:43,400
Didn't you tell me that
the source of intel could be trusted?

531
00:34:43,480 --> 00:34:44,639
It is.

532
00:34:44,800 --> 00:34:48,400
However, you were the one to verify
the contents of this contract.

533
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:50,600
You were too impatient.

534
00:34:50,679 --> 00:34:52,480
Ling Yizhou is very cunning.

535
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:53,800
I'm impatient?

536
00:34:53,880 --> 00:34:56,159
If I'm not,
how can I take down Ling Yizhou?

537
00:34:58,920 --> 00:35:00,480
Our collaboration ends here.

538
00:35:01,440 --> 00:35:02,320
Mr. Jin!

539
00:35:03,840 --> 00:35:04,880
I'm warning you.

540
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:07,400
Don't think about trying anything
behind my back.

541
00:35:07,800 --> 00:35:10,480
I have dirt on you.

542
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:38,720
It's so hot.

543
00:35:38,960 --> 00:35:40,320
An iced drink sounds nice.

544
00:35:52,520 --> 00:35:54,960
LINGSHI GROUP

545
00:35:57,920 --> 00:35:59,400
Boss, here's your coffee.

546
00:36:00,600 --> 00:36:01,640
MUZHOU

547
00:36:02,200 --> 00:36:04,080
You don't want coffee today?
I'll get tea for you.

548
00:36:04,520 --> 00:36:05,360
Come back here.

549
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:14,640
"Muzhou"?

550
00:36:15,160 --> 00:36:16,960
Boss, when did you get a new phone case?

551
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:19,400
Mumu gave it to me.

552
00:36:20,520 --> 00:36:21,920
Ms. Xia has great taste.

553
00:36:24,080 --> 00:36:25,320
Obviously.

554
00:36:27,400 --> 00:36:30,080
Don't you think the two figures here
look like me and Mumu?

555
00:36:30,200 --> 00:36:31,360
Let me see.

556
00:36:31,680 --> 00:36:34,120
I think they do.

557
00:36:34,760 --> 00:36:35,880
Was this drawn by hand?

558
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:37,400
It's nicely done.

559
00:36:37,480 --> 00:36:39,120
Look, it fits my phone.

560
00:36:40,160 --> 00:36:41,880
There are only two.
One for Mumu, one for me.

561
00:36:41,960 --> 00:36:42,960
Are you trying to take it?

562
00:36:43,480 --> 00:36:44,800
You can keep it.

563
00:36:46,440 --> 00:36:47,920
You won't give me a raise either.

564
00:36:49,240 --> 00:36:50,520
The artist is quite talented.

565
00:36:51,560 --> 00:36:52,680
It's nicely done.

566
00:36:53,920 --> 00:36:54,880
Very talented.

567
00:37:05,920 --> 00:37:09,760
Wen Li, how is the sales performance
for our department stores this quarter?

568
00:37:16,120 --> 00:37:18,880
Promotions attracted many customers
who aren't members.

569
00:37:21,360 --> 00:37:24,320
When do you think we should begin
promoting sales for the next quarter?

570
00:37:25,120 --> 00:37:29,800
I arranged next season's sales
to begin on the 16th of next month.

571
00:37:36,920 --> 00:37:39,920
Boss, Mr. Jin has tendered
his resignation.

572
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:41,840
A wise course of action.

573
00:37:45,200 --> 00:37:46,280
Get rid of this.

574
00:37:46,720 --> 00:37:47,600
Okay.

575
00:37:47,920 --> 00:37:51,000
Without the help of this bug
in the phone case,

576
00:37:51,400 --> 00:37:53,320
we would've needed
several different contingency plans.

577
00:37:53,400 --> 00:37:55,520
This won't be as simple as we think.

578
00:37:57,120 --> 00:38:00,680
That's why we have another priority
at the moment.

579
00:38:01,600 --> 00:38:02,600
Yes, Boss.

580
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:24,280
<i>Let's get back on topic.</i>

581
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:27,080
<i>Why are you rejecting Mr. Ling?</i>

582
00:38:27,560 --> 00:38:30,920
He's handsome, comes from a good family
and devoted to you.

583
00:38:31,240 --> 00:38:33,680
Isn't he the perfect husband?

584
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:35,320
Why are you rejecting him?

585
00:38:36,120 --> 00:38:37,080
What's the matter?

586
00:38:39,240 --> 00:38:41,040
I'll forgive you this time.

587
00:38:41,960 --> 00:38:44,520
You're not allowed to go
with anybody else next time.

588
00:38:46,280 --> 00:38:47,280
Got it?

589
00:38:52,680 --> 00:38:54,640
The perfect husband?

590
00:38:55,520 --> 00:38:56,880
How perfect is he?

591
00:38:57,520 --> 00:38:58,840
I will not

592
00:38:59,040 --> 00:39:03,520
be swayed by Ling Yizhou's charms.

593
00:39:15,800 --> 00:39:16,720
Coming.

594
00:39:20,920 --> 00:39:22,840
-What are you doing here?
-I'm picking you up.

595
00:39:23,280 --> 00:39:24,920
Didn't you agree to move in with me?

596
00:39:25,120 --> 00:39:26,720
When did I say that?

597
00:39:28,280 --> 00:39:29,520
After what we've done,

598
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:31,480
aren't you going to take responsibility?

599
00:39:32,480 --> 00:39:33,880
There are so many who would do that.

600
00:39:33,960 --> 00:39:34,960
Why do you need me?

601
00:39:35,040 --> 00:39:36,120
You're different.

602
00:39:36,680 --> 00:39:39,000
No way. We were photographed last time.

603
00:39:39,200 --> 00:39:41,400
What if I get photographed again
moving in with you?

604
00:39:41,720 --> 00:39:42,960
You don't have to worry about that.

605
00:39:43,280 --> 00:39:45,200
You and Boss are engaged.

606
00:39:45,280 --> 00:39:48,000
Even if you're photographed,
Muzhou fans will lap it up.

607
00:39:48,080 --> 00:39:49,360
So your argument is moot.

608
00:39:52,960 --> 00:39:54,280
I have a lot of things.

609
00:39:54,360 --> 00:39:55,760
Moving back and forth will be a hassle.

610
00:39:55,840 --> 00:39:57,360
Besides, you live so far from my office.

611
00:39:57,920 --> 00:40:00,080
This is a valid argument, isn't it?

612
00:40:00,880 --> 00:40:01,760
Yes.

613
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:03,560
You're right, Mumu.

614
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:06,040
All right, I understand.

615
00:40:08,080 --> 00:40:08,920
You...

616
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:10,920
I didn't say you could come in!
What are you doing?

617
00:40:11,440 --> 00:40:12,880
You're really going to stay here?

618
00:40:18,080 --> 00:40:20,000
-You...
-Since it's inconvenient for you to move,

619
00:40:20,080 --> 00:40:21,520
I'll move here.

620
00:40:21,760 --> 00:40:23,640
This saves you the trouble of packing.

621
00:40:23,720 --> 00:40:25,280
You won't have to adjust
to a new environment

622
00:40:25,360 --> 00:40:26,760
and this place is close to your office.

623
00:40:28,120 --> 00:40:29,080
You...

624
00:40:33,760 --> 00:40:36,800
You had it all planned out.

625
00:40:42,800 --> 00:40:44,040
You're right, Mumu.

626
00:40:44,720 --> 00:40:46,720
I do have plans for you.

627
00:40:52,600 --> 00:40:54,680
It'll be inconvenient
for you to live here.

628
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:57,400
Are you worried about me?

629
00:40:57,880 --> 00:40:59,800
-Any examples?
-Your lifestyle habits.

630
00:41:00,160 --> 00:41:01,480
You don't need to worry about that.

631
00:41:01,560 --> 00:41:03,000
Boss can adapt easily.

632
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:05,320
This place is far from your office.

633
00:41:05,480 --> 00:41:06,680
Don't worry about that either.

634
00:41:06,840 --> 00:41:08,680
I will be driving him to work every day.

635
00:41:09,880 --> 00:41:11,760
Pidan lives here. Isn't he afraid of dogs?

636
00:41:11,840 --> 00:41:12,760
That's--

637
00:41:13,240 --> 00:41:14,120
I know.

638
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:16,040
Pidan and I are great friends now.

639
00:41:21,280 --> 00:41:22,360
Right, Pidan?

640
00:41:27,720 --> 00:41:30,040
You traitor.

641
00:41:31,280 --> 00:41:33,760
Boss, since you're moving in today,

642
00:41:33,840 --> 00:41:37,360
should we invite Ms. Jia
for a housewarming party?

643
00:41:38,040 --> 00:41:39,360
What do you think, Mumu?

644
00:41:42,240 --> 00:41:43,360
Get out!

645
00:43:30,240 --> 00:43:31,240
Let's begin the meeting.

646
00:43:42,920 --> 00:43:44,280
I can't believe it.

647
00:45:21,040 --> 00:45:21,960
What's wrong?

648
00:45:26,680 --> 00:45:28,000
Where's the steering wheel?

649
00:45:30,480 --> 00:45:34,520
Have you seen my steering wheel?

650
00:45:35,600 --> 00:45:37,240
Where's your steering wheel?

651
00:45:37,400 --> 00:45:38,560
I need to drive home.

652
00:45:38,640 --> 00:45:41,000
I need the steering wheel to do that.

653
00:45:41,080 --> 00:45:43,720
-Where's my steering wheel?
-The wheel is right in front of you.

654
00:45:43,840 --> 00:45:45,160
Just reach out.

655
00:45:45,520 --> 00:45:47,640
Do you see it? It's right in front of you.

656
00:45:49,520 --> 00:45:52,360
-Yes, right there.
-Here it is.

657
00:45:53,360 --> 00:45:55,920
Hold it and you can drive.

658
00:45:56,080 --> 00:45:58,000
I know how to drive.

659
00:45:59,640 --> 00:46:01,640
Subtitle translation by Renee Luk
